    • gotName

      boolean gotName
      If the UI got the name of the player that means all information is filled in to start a new game. If not the player clicked cancel at some point of the process and there is not enough information to start the game.

    • start_game

      void start_game()
      Queries the player for more information to start the game. If all is filled in, the Board is loaded and server is contacted to start the game. Starts the original deck game.

    • start_gameRandom

      void start_gameRandom()
      Queries the player for more information to start the game. If all is filled in, the Board is loaded and server is contacted to start the game. Starts the random deck game.

    • show_dialog_HowManyPlayers

      private boolean show_dialog_HowManyPlayers()
      Shows dialog asking the player how many players overall he wants to have in the game.
      Returns:
      True if the dialog is filled and OK is selected. False is the dialog is cancelled.

    • show_dialog_InsertYourName

      private void show_dialog_InsertYourName()
      Shows a dialog window to ask the player about his name. If the name is filled in and OK is pressed, variable to enable continuation is set.

    • show_dialog_howManyAI

      private void show_dialog_howManyAI()
      Shows a dialog to ask the player how many AIs hw wishes to have in game. If the player did not choose single player mode for testing, he may choose how many AIs he wants to play with.
